Cook tortellini according to package directions. Meanwhile, heat oil in a skillet; cook zucchini, squash, onion, red pepper and spices until vegetables are crisp-tender. Drain tortellini and rinse in hot water; combine with vegetables mixture, mozzarella and cream in a 1-1/2-qt. baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 375 degrees F for 20 minutes or until heated through.